body:
@swagle  This is old branch-2.6 achitecture. I don't like it. And it's quite hacky for autostart. So this is just one more hack solution on top of that. In that arch  we were sending configs for autostart with status command as a separate field.

For 2.7 in scope of perf changes I totally redone it. And it works pretty nice, repos and everything is present. All the data which is used there is from general events: metadata/hpl/topology/configs

Regarding your question i think install was done as usual so repos were present. So autostart could work, unless we need to install lzo during start of hdfs components. In that case we generate HDP-GPL repo.
retest this please
